================================================================================
Clean-room notice
================================================================================

The interactive CLI shell under shell/ is a clean-room implementation.

Its design was informed only by the *concepts* and the *public API behaviour* of
the Zephyr RTOS shell (a Linux Foundation project, Apache-2.0) and -- for the
line editor -- by the behaviour of GNU readline / linenoise / bash. No source
code, comments, or specific wording from Zephyr (or any of those projects) was
copied. Zephyr was used as a design reference only; none of its code is present
in this repository.

All shell source files (shell/) are original work under the MIT License, carrying
the header:

    SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
    Copyright (c) 2026 ThreadX Shell Project

